# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Units
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:unit-3309
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Digital writing"@en ;
  curric:slug "digital-writing" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit covers various aspects of using a computer to create and manipulate
  text. Pupils will become familiar with using a keyboard and mouse to enter and remove
  text. They will consider how to change the look of their text, and will be able to justify
  their reasoning for making these changes."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit develops pupils’ skills in creating and editing digital content
  with a word processor. They will improve typing accuracy, learn to navigate keys efficiently
  and refine design choices for clarity and impact. Alongside the previous unit, this builds
  essential computer skills that help pupils access, record, and present their learning
  effectively by using technology as a tool to support what they do.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3309-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3309-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3309-3 ;
  curric:id "3309"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.061226Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-computing-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-creating-media ,
    oakcurric:thread-effective-use-of-tools .

oakcurric:unit-3310
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Creating animations in programs"@en ;
  curric:slug "creating-animations-in-programs" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils are introduced to on-screen programming through ScratchJr.
  Pupils will explore the way a project looks onscreen by investigating sprites and
  backgrounds. They will use programming blocks to use, modify, and create programs that
  move objects."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces pupils to how computer programs are built and carry
  out actions. Using block-based programming they explore controlling sprites, selecting
  backgrounds and creating or adapting projects, alongside designing simple algorithms. This is
  the first step in developing computational thinking, giving pupils the foundations in logic,
  sequencing, and problem solving that will be revisited and expanded upon.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3310-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3310-2 ;
  curric:id "3310"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.228768Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-computing-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-programming ,
    oakcurric:thread-design-and-development .

oakcurric:unit-3313
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Building sequences in programs"@en ;
  curric:slug "building-sequences-in-programs" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils will begin to understand that sequences of commands have an
  outcome and will start to make predictions about what these outcomes may be. Pupils will
  use and modify designs to create their own quiz questions using sequences of code blocks."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ previous experiences with block-based
  programming to deepen their understanding of how sequences of commands produce outcomes. They
  learn to predict and explain code behaviour, recognising how small changes affect results. By
  designing and modifying quiz questions, pupils take an early step in structured
  problem-solving, laying the groundwork for more complex programming concepts and applications
  in later years.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3313-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3313-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3313-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3313-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3313-5 ;
  curric:id "3313"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.230679Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-computing-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-programming ,
    oakcurric:thread-design-and-development .

oakcurric:unit-3308
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Digital painting"@en ;
  curric:slug "digital-painting" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils develop their understanding of how to manipulate digital
  devices by using painting tools. They practise by creating digital paintings, gaining
  inspiration from the work of artists whilst reflecting on their preferences when painting
  with and without the use of digital devices."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces pupils to using digital tools for the first time. It
  builds their confidence and foundational skills in operating digital devices. Before
  starting, pupils should already know how to turn on and log in to their device. Throughout
  the unit, they will develop key digital skills they’ll use across the curriculum. In later
  units these same skills will support pupils as they explore different ways to create and edit
  digital images and apply these same skills across a range of applications.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3308-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3308-2 ;
  curric:id "3308"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.426161Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-computing-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-creating-media ,
    oakcurric:thread-effective-use-of-tools .

oakcurric:unit-3312
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Using IT to organise and present data"@en ;
  curric:slug "using-it-to-organise-and-present-data" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will explore what the term data means and how data can be
  collected. They will explore how attributes can be used to organise data and how data can
  be presented in the form of pictograms and block diagrams. Pupils will use the data
  presented to answer questions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Having previously explored how to collect, summarise and present data,
  pupils now develop their skills in organising and classifying information. They refine their
  ability to identify attributes, ask precise yes/no questions and sort objects, strengthening
  logical thinking and decision-making. This progression builds the foundation for analysing,
  comparing and structuring data preparing pupils for more complex tasks involving patterns,
  problem-solving, and drawing conclusions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3312-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3312-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3312-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3312-4 ;
  curric:id "3312"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.575299Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-computing-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-data-and-information ,
    oakcurric:thread-effective-use-of-tools .

oakcurric:unit-3311
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Information technology in the world beyond school"@en ;
  curric:slug "information-technology-in-the-world-beyond-school" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils develop their understanding of what information technology is
  and will begin to identify examples. Pupils will discuss where they have seen IT in school
  and beyond. They will investigate how IT improves our world whilst also recognising the
  importance of using IT responsibly."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit progresses pupils' knowledge and understanding of technology and
  how they interact with it both in school and the wider world. They will build their knowledge
  of what Information Technology is and how it is used day-to-day. They will also consider the
  appropriate use of IT, setting the expectation that it should be used carefully and
  responsibly throughout their lives.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3311-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3311-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3311-3 ;
  curric:id "3311"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.781368Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-computing-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-networks ,
    oakcurric:thread-computing-systems ,
    oakcurric:thread-safety-and-security .

